      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>Identify each of the colored positions—red, blue, and green—as axial or equatorial. Then carry out a ring-flip, and show the new positions occupied by each color.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBaFlSIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--4bfaee59a06b3e3646b89774c607b91e4e17c10b/OChem_04_06_008.jpg\" alt=\"Ball and stick model of substituted cyclohexane with red, blue, and green spheres at C1, C3, and C6 undergoes ring-flip to form model with all substituents, represented by white circles.\">",
